    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document specifies a symmetric key format for the transport and provisioning of symmetric keys to different types of crypto modules.  For example, One-Time Password (OTP) shared secrets or symmetric cryptographic keys to strong authentication devices.  A standard key transport format enables enterprises to deploy best-of-breed solutions combining components from different vendors into the same infrastructure. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
